Description from Google Play:
Key features:
- View and play music by album, artist, genre, song, playlists, folders, and album artists;
- Viewing and video playback;
- Automatically download missing album artwork, artist pictures and genre illustrations;
- Manual selection of relevant album artwork, artist pictures, genre illustrations from the Internet, the Gallery app, ID3-tags, or album folder;
- Change the user interface of the player, set one of the 14 available skins, all free of charge;
- Set the layout view between Grid or List;
- Reading the reviews of the album and artist;
- Download, search and save LYRICS to your music files using standard ID3-tags;
- Single and group TAG EDITING: title, album, artist, track, year, genre, comment. Supported formats: mp3, ogg, flac, wma, wav, m4a, mp4;
- Miscellaneous audio effects for Android devices&gt; 2, 3, 5-band graphic equalizer with default / customizable presets (edit, rename, delete), STEREO EXTENSION effect (virtualizer), REVERB effects (large hall, medium hall, plate, small room, medium room, large room), BASS BOOST effect, volume control;
- Free add DSP PLUGIN for Android = 2.3 devices: 10 band graphic equalizer with 15 default / customizable presets, PRE-AMP control, bass boost, volume control. Go to Settings&gt; Audio and select &quot;Download DSP pack&quot; to install the free plugin;
- Sound Effects Dolby and SRS for HTC devices equipped with improved sound HTC (HTC Desire HD, etc.).
- SMART statistics and music playlists: ratings, number of plays / passes Losing last, last added;
- Import and export music history and ratings from your favorite desktop music player: Songbird, Winamp, Wmp, MediaMonkey, music files;
- Selection of music folders;
- Choice of 2 LOCK SCREEN widgets with many customization options: unlock slider, sound switch, skip tracks using volume buttons, gestures;
- Choice of 5 different home screen widgets (4x1, 2x2, 3x3, 4x4, 4x2);
- Scrobbling support: Simple Last.fm, Scrobble Droid, official app Last.fm;
- Sleep timer with a gradual decay;
- Sending text notifications, album covers / artist in your favorite social networks: Twitter, Facebook, Gmail, Picassa, etc.;
- Headset support. Customize long press and actions double / triple clicking;
- Search for a library. Voice search;
- Gestures (player: swipe album art to skip songs, view: swipe left to play next, swipe right to play last);
- SHAKE feature: Shake your phone to play next / previous song (eg: shake top to bottom or bottom to top to play next / previous song);
- Create shortcuts to playlists;
- Support APP2SD.
